## When to Refactor
- Before adding new features to an area with tech debt
- When a file exceeds ~300 lines
- When you need to copy-paste to implement something
- On a regular schedule (e.g., first Friday of each month)

## Refactoring Checklist
- [ ] Tests pass before refactoring
- [ ] Refactor in a separate PR (never mix with feature work)
- [ ] Tests still pass after refactoring
- [ ] No behavior changes — only structure changes
- [ ] Update ADR if architecture changes
